    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl>E.Zimi in <ptr target="#wilson1999"/>, pp. <citedRange>161-163</citedRange> (no image)</bibl>, and 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cdlBE"/>, <citedRange>2000.743</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>49.2353 a</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>089100</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><w lemma="μισθός"><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">μ</supplied>ισθὸς</w> <w lemma="οἰκία">οἰκία<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">ς</supplied></w>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="1">
                        <lem resp="#cdlBE"><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">μ</supplied>ισθὸς οἰκία<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">ς</supplied></lem>
                        <rdg resp="#wilson1999"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>ισθος <orig>οικια</orig><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Loyer de la maison (?)</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Rent for the house (?)</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Pigione per la casa (?)</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>تأجير للمنزل</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
             <p>No other Greek word occurs to the mind for <foreign xml:lang="grc"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>ισθος</foreign> than <foreign xml:lang="grc">μισθός</foreign>, which sometimes means 'rent' 
                    especially in Egyptian papyri; however this reading remains unsure as long as no photograph of the sherd is available.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
